## 1. Startup Protocol

1. Read only `docs/entrypoint.md` first.
2. Summarize the current state in 5-7 lines.
3. Pull only the files needed for that summary: typically `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`, `docs/operations/shared-instructions.md`, and `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`.
4. Pull other files only when {{USER_NAME}}'s question or task requires them.
5. For task-time behavior use `docs/operations/session-kickoff.md`; for explicit time estimates use `docs/operations/time-estimation.md`. Neither is a startup file unless the task needs it.
6. When answering {{USER_NAME}}, lead with a concise 1-3 line conclusion in {{CHAT_LANG}}.
7. Define technical terms briefly on first use; use `docs/concepts/glossary.md` if terminology is uncertain.

This framework does not use Project Memory; the docs tree under `docs/` is the single source of truth, gated by `make docs-check`. When generating a Claude Code prompt, re-check section 0 and `docs/operations/rules/operational-constraints.md`. Do not reconstruct path values, operational-constraint wording, or current code tokens from chat-recalled memory; verify against current files with rg / view.

