## 5. Change Routing

Use this section when editing docs. Pick the first file from section 5.1, then verify the cascade in section 5.2. Update cascade files only when the edited claim, path, rule, or status affects them.

### 5.1 First File To Edit

| Change type | Edit first | Then check |
|---|---|---|
| Startup protocol or Project Instructions behavior | `docs/operations/project-memory-and-instructions.md` and the `docs/entrypoint.md` mirror | `docs/operations/shared-instructions.md`, `docs/operations/rules/operating-principles.md`, `docs/operations/session-kickoff.md`, `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md` |
| Path variables or path-writing policy | `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0 | `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`, `docs/operations/directory-map.md`, `docs/operations/rules/operational-constraints.md` |
| Current {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}, verdict, next task | `docs/project/project-status.md` | `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`, `docs/project/backlog/README.md`, `docs/operations/session-kickoff.md` |
| Numeric result or metric | `docs/evaluation/comparison.md` | `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`, `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md` |
| New backlog item or next idea | `docs/project/backlog/README.md` and the relevant body | `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md` |
| {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} creation or status change | `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md` | `docs/project/themes/theme-bodies.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-rules.md` |
| Method, objective, or evaluation design | the relevant file under `docs/method/` or `docs/evaluation/` | `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`, `docs/project/project-status.md` |
| Operating rule, forbidden action, or deliverable policy | the relevant file under `docs/operations/rules/` | `docs/operations/shared-instructions.md`, `docs/operations/session-kickoff.md`, `docs/operations/operation-modes.md` |
| README or related-work claim | the relevant file under `docs/writing/` | `docs/concepts/core-concepts.md`, the relevant method docs, `docs/evaluation/comparison.md` |

